<note xml:id="ch49n49"><p id="ch49n49pa1">The Venetian historians, John Sagorninus (Chron. Venet. p. 13) and the doge Andrew Dandolo (Scriptores Rer. Ital. tom. xii. p. 135), have preserved this epistle of Gregory. The loss and recovery of Ravenna are mentioned by Paulus Diaconus (de Gest. Langobard. l. vi. c. 49, 54, in Script. Ital. tom. i. pars i. p. 506, 508); but our chronologists, Pagi, Muratori, &amp;c. cannot ascertain the date or circumstances. [Monticolo, Le spedizioni di Liutprando, &amp;c., in the Arch. d. R. Soc. Rom. di storia patria (1892), p. 321 <hi rend="italic">sqq.;</hi> Hodgkin, op. cit. vi. note F. p. 505-8. The date of the recovery of Ravenna was probably <span class="sc"><span class="entity ad">ad</span></span> 740, that of the capture <span class="sc"><span class="entity ad">ad</span></span> 738 or 739; but Monticolo places both in <span class="sc"><span class="entity ad">ad</span></span> 735.]</p></note>

